{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She cups her hands and yells up to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hikes down the hill, squishing down the water plants, almost falling, the first time we've seen him happy in his own skin.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 36 EXT. SUNSET BOULEVARD -- LATER NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miss Penny Lane's yellow Vega makes the big swing onto Sunset Boulevard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sings along to the obscure words of Led Zeppelin's "Dancing Days."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William takes it all in from the passenger seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Huge billboards advertise not cigarettes or beer, but albums.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a wondrous piece of geography for any rock fan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shot moves in as William, watches, takes it all in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves his head outside the window to see fully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her windshield is cracked along the side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PENNY LANE
{DIALOGUE}: The Continental Hyatt House.
