{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Up ahead, the door to their smallish hotel room is open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside, a band party in full swing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A clunky early-model boom box segues from James Brown's "Make It Funky" to Led Zeppelin's "Gallows Pole."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell Hammond is the center of this party, jabbing out the chords, playing along on guitar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Much singing echoes all around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a hotel-room Hootenanny, and all members of the band are present.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Penny Lane takes a breath and enters, with arms extended and pointing in opposite directions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She does a flawless stewardess imitation, with proper hand gestures, to a loud party ovation.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PENNY LANE (cont'd)
