{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{META_DATA}: (as in "you're on of us")
{DIALOGUE}: GO AWAY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She shuts the door quickly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It hurts a little.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up the wadded pieces of paper, stuffs them in his pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaves the door and helps himself to some soap and pencils and matches from the nearby maid's cart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he returns to Russell's door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can't help but listen to the muffled sounds of laughter, just for a moment, escalating.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He flips the sign over: HOUSEKEEPING PLEASE ENTER - CLEAN ROOM.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 62 INT. OUTER RADIO STATION - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Humble Pie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Thirty Days in the Hole."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell and band enter the radio station, passing through the now-empty front office.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As always, Russell sets the tone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's feeling good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stillwater takes over -- they feel mighty, like the Beetles, as they climb across chairs, rearrange wall hangings and gold records and head down the small hallway to the control room interview.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rolling with the flow are William and Penny in her green coat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries to distance himself from her -- still a little stung by the earlier hallway rebuff -- but she will have none of it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She privately shares every great passing moment with him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries not to succumb to these charms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Music segues to Stillwater's own "Fever Dog."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 63 INT. RADIO CONTROL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stillwater's own record spins, and it sounds good to everyone in this room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell takes a seat near the open mike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jeff Bebe is quick to take the other seat, arranging himself to be just as close to the microphone as Russell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William watches all as he sits at the dark back of this control booth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stillwater sits with late-night progressive disc-jockey QUINCE ALLEN, 25.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince takes a long hit from a joint and does not pass it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The entire Stillwater band is now collected in the studio and ready for the interview.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William can't avoid looking at Penny Lane, who looks great tonight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She catches him, and he barely looks away in time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Polexia, newly reconciled with Jeff, notices.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The very mellow disc-jockey eases up to the microphone, as the finale of "Fever Dog" is just ending.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: QUINCE ALLEN
{DIALOGUE}: The guitar of Russell Hammond.
{DIALOGUE}: "Fever Dog"... The band is Stillwater.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Watch with your mind as they materialize.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Band members gets closer to the microphone, preparing to speak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince lowers his head, shutting his eyes and getting into the music as the song plays out.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 64 INT. HOTEL ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The phone rings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Estrella answers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ESTRELLA
{DIALOGUE}: William's room.
