{DIALOGUE}: Here.
{DIALOGUE}: Live.
{DIALOGUE}: It's the Night Circus.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The band scoots closer to the microphone, ready to talk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince continues, looking meaningfully at the band.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are waiting... eager for a chance to speak.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: QUINCE (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Every minute a baby is born somewhere.
{DIALOGUE}: Life.
{DIALOGUE}: Death.
{DIALOGUE}: Hermetically sealed bags of human emotion.
{DIALOGUE}: Bags of love... bags of kindness?
{META_DATA}: (suddenly, turns)
{DIALOGUE}: How'd you get together?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Jeff eagerly speaks, Quince lowers his head and listens... feels... the words of his guests.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: Well... not to get into a "me" thing... this is Jeff talking... but I did start the band, some time, actually, ago.
{DIALOGUE}: This is back when we were the Jeff Bebe band, and I placed an ad in a magazine called Peaches looking for a guitarist and Russell Hammond answered.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince nods, head bowed, swaying slowly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: QUINCE
{META_DATA}: (with deep understanding)
{DIALOGUE}: Peaches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jeff watches Quince's head lower.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's hard to know when to talk with Quince.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The depth of his mellowness is tough to get in rhythm with.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: I think he was a gift from God, actually.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody plays like Russell Hammond.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{META_DATA}: (sorta moved)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, shit.
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He instantly realizes he's slipped, on the air.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Ooops.
{DIALOGUE}: Better hit the delay button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All eyes turn to Quince, whose head stays down, grooving to some inner beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He says nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The band looks at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We become increasingly aware that Quince may now be asleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Long silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William shares an amazed look with Penny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince is definitely asleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell leans forward and continues talking quietly, with hilarious sincerity.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay - we're talking now, right?
{DIALOGUE}: Why the fuck do you wait until and interview in Arizona to say something nice about me.
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you say it to my fucking face sometime?
{DIALOGUE}: Because I tell you every time I think you nailed something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody pays you compliments.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not my fucking job to kiss your fucking ass all the time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: Well then who's fucking job is it?
{DIALOGUE}: Because my ass is dying for a kiss.
{DIALOGUE}: And I know yours is too.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: It's my fucking job.
{DIALOGUE}: You're all geniuses.
{DIALOGUE}: And let me just add this thought - smegma.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Penny covers her mouth as offers a look of absurdity to William.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He offers one back, as laughs are stifled throughout the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William shares a look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince is still deeply asleep, as the usually quiet tony leans forward to speak.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: Feces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He cracks himself up, silently.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quince snaps awake, fully in- stride.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: QUINCE
{DIALOGUE}: The dong is called "Love Thing."
{DIALOGUE}: Your mind is Starting to take effect.
{DIALOGUE}: They're all here to see you swallow fire.
{DIALOGUE}: You scream soundlessly... on the Night Circus.
{DIALOGUE}: It's Quince, with Stillwater.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Love Thing" takes over, as Quince swivels in the chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: QUINCE (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: I thought that went well.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 66 INT. RENTAL CAR -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Adrenalized laughter.
