{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 92 INT. TOUR BUS -- MORNING - 5 AM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Tiny Dancer" continues on the bus stereo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell sits up front, swathed in a large robe, alone and silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others have given him a wide berth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He feels silly, and they know it, and he hates that they know it, which makes him feel foolish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits silently.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William watches him from four rows back, next to Penny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She kisses the top of his forehead, a hero's welcome.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He yawns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The song's vocal begins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is only more silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, after a beat, we hear a voice or two, fighting the quiet and singing along.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then others... waking up... joining in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then Jeff.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell hears them and starts to sing along too, louder now, without turning around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a voice everyone wants to hear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Like it or not, this is his family.
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 93 EXT. HIGHWAY -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Passing signs announce Greenville, North Carolina.
