{DIALOGUE}: -- back here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The band looks at Dick, who manages not to be speechless.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: But why should we pay you for something we can do ourselves?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE
{META_DATA}: (immediately)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know how to keep from getting charged for the ice below the floorboards of Chicago Stadium?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know how to do a headlining tour, do you Claire Rothman at the L.A. Forum?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know Bobbi Cowan, Lisa Robinson, Jim Ladd, Frank Barcelona?
{META_DATA}: (look around, amazed)
{DIALOGUE}: This is Cleveland.
{DIALOGUE}: Where's Kid Leo??
{META_DATA}: (basics)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know how you get a record not pressed but played?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know?
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't invent the rainy day, man.
{DIALOGUE}: I just own the best umbrella.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He laughs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's fun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Band members are now listening, curiously spellbound.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Because as much as you may believe that it will last forever, it does not last forever... your biggest fan right now soon they're going to go to college, gonna wanna buy clothes, spend that money some other way, and you know what?
{META_DATA}: (the final insult)
{DIALOGUE}: They'll tape your record from a friend's copy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell stops fingering his guitar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shot moves across the faces of the band members.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: You've got to take what you can, when you can, while you can.
{DIALOGUE}: And you've got to do it now.
{DIALOGUE}: That's what the big boys do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The band squirms, but listens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Because if you think Mick Jagger will still be out there trying to be a rock star at age fifty, you're sadly sadly mistaken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now he's reaching them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their slackened roar-weary faces stare back at the young dynamo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{META_DATA}: (flustered)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, well... we'll think about what you said.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE
{META_DATA}: (casually)
{DIALOGUE}: No no.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't understand.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll think about it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not auditioning.
{DIALOGUE}: I came here to decide whether I want to represent you.
{DIALOGUE}: So I'll stand outside for a moment, and think about whether I want to stay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaves the room with a pleasant shrug.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stunned silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William watches their body language.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one wants to talk first.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their faces read as -- who was that guy, and how can we talk him into staying?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 113 INT. PLANE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William watches as the band stands inside the new plane.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dennis Hope looks on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: This is not us.
{DIALOGUE}: This is too much.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks around for support.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grim nodding faces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{META_DATA}: (impressed at seat)
{DIALOGUE}: This is too much.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William watches as Russell reclines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell grabs Penny, and she falls into the seat next to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the loud oncoming sound of the plane in flight, as Dennis cooly asks for Penny's seat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE
{DIALOGUE}: Do you mind?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 114 EXT. PRIVATE AIRPORT -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doris the bus stays behind in the parking lot, abandoned near a field.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The new plane lifts off in the background, as the bus sits alone, as if crying steel tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bus Banner reads simply: CLEVELAND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reprise ending of Whole Lotta Love.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 115 INT. PLANE NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The girls sit on the jumper seats at the back of the plane, with William.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 116 INT. BOSTON HOTEL ROOM HALLWAY -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William trudges the hallway with tape-recorder and notebook, trolling for Russell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He passes Boston travelogue posters on the walls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few room doors are open, he looks for any sign of the guitarist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William veers into Dick's room, where a poker game full of Roadies is in progress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room is thick with exotic smoke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are a bunch of road-hardened snobs, smoking cigars and other items, famous to themselves, listening not to rock and roll... but Sarah Vaughn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: Anyone seen Russell?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: The Enemy!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Door widens to reveal Russell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: Hey!
{DIALOGUE}: Welcome to the Road Crew Poker Party.
{DIALOGUE}: This game's been going of for two years.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: That's Mick - he's with The Who.
{DIALOGUE}: That's John - with J. Geils.
{DIALOGUE}: And that's Richard with the Eagles... and you know The Wheel.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THE WHEEL
{DIALOGUE}: Hey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grumbling roadies continue playing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Like an old pro, the kid turns down a Cola-can hash-pipe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This hand is down to Dick, and a roadie named REG from Humble Pie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: Side proposition.
{DIALOGUE}: For fifty dollars and a case of Heineken, I will put into the pot... three Lovely Ladies, Including the famous Penny Lane... the Band-Aids, who need to exit our tour before New York...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REG
{DIALOGUE}: It's a deal.
{DIALOGUE}: Show 'em.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dick lays down three tens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reg lays down three Kings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dick loses.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: Three Lovely Ladies... now in the custody of Humble Pie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REG
{DIALOGUE}: Alright, so we owe you fifty dollars and a case of Heineken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Embarrassed, Russell notices the kids face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans over, and speaks confidentially to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: Look.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody's feelings are getting hurt here.
{DIALOGUE}: She already knows Leslie's coming To New York tomorrow.
{DIALOGUE}: They all understand.
{DIALOGUE}: This is the Circus.
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody's trying not to go home.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody's saying goodbye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: No, I got it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: These are the Rules that come with every electric Guitar and every amplifier.
{DIALOGUE}: They're not just written anywhere.
{DIALOGUE}: Rock and roll, brother.
{DIALOGUE}: No attachments.
{DIALOGUE}: No boundaries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But the kid feels bad, and Russell knows it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Quit looking at me like that.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 116A INT. HALLWAY - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kid is still stuck on the road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is in hell now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wearily, with deep circles under his eyes, he shuts his eyes for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another band is moving through.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SABBATH ROADIE
{DIALOGUE}: Keep this hallway clear!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 117 INT. BACKSTAGE TRAILER/DRESSING ROOM -- AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William and Penny sit on opposite ends of a blue locker-room bench.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a small dressing room, crowded with roadies, guitars and men in stages of half-dress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Piles of luggage headed for New York sit by the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door suddenly opens and Dick arrives with champagne and a cake decorated with a sparkler.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is placed in Penny's lap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It reads: Unforgettable Penny... Age Unknown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boston, 1973.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They gather now as the cake sits before a surprised and enchanted Penny Lane.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: Happy Birthday from us.
