{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: She says she's retired Though we've heard that before.
{DIALOGUE}: She chose us... And in Penny Lane we trust She is a fan of this band.
{DIALOGUE}: Much more so than us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William watches her face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still enchanted, she hands out slices of the cake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE
{META_DATA}: (to the point)
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry the plane isn't bigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It hits her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks at William for a clue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His truthful face does not look away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now she knows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns to the others -- the plane isn't bigger?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shot moves in on Penny as she blinks just a little, cutting into the cake, still mugging for everybody, covering it all with a layer of sweet giddy laughter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shot comes to rest behind her, her head turning to connect with band members.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Each of them look away, nobody maintaining eye contact with her except the one she now doesn't look at.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She blows out the candles, vamping Marilyn Monroe-style, and sucks off the frosting seductively, to cheers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell watches, as we push in on Penny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She notices all the luggage is gone, only her two cases remain by the door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 118 EXT. CONCORD PAVILLION BACKSTAGE -- EARLY MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William exits a backstage Portosan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Penny catches him by the grilling area where catering is preparing for the outdoor event.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their laminated passes swing from around their necks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thuding in the distance, Stillwater plays for a cheering outdoor crowd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of summer insects in the air.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PENNY
{DIALOGUE}: So it wasn't a birthday party, it was a farewell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William doesn't answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at her, blowing some hair out of her face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PENNY (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: You think you can fool me.
