{META_DATA}: (taking treatment for granted)
{DIALOGUE}: ThanksI'llseeyoulater.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nearby, the young journalist studies the tour's subtle shift in welcoming Leslie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dick's New York side is almost military.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: Bags in five!
{DIALOGUE}: Cars leave for the party at six!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William studies Leslie, everyone saying hello to her, everyone knowing the subtext.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nobody saying a word.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William pulls his heavy bag out of the back of the limousine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bag breaks, and the contents spill out onto the New York sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bars of soap, ashtrays, hotel keys, crumpled paper, the contraband t-shirt, "Do Not Disturb" signs, notes, towels and thick telephone books from every city.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: You know.
{DIALOGUE}: There are lighter souvenirs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{META_DATA}: (embarrassed)
