{DIALOGUE}: The Enemy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They shake, she smiles randomly.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 126 INT. ST. REGIS FRONT DESK -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William checks in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLERK
{DIALOGUE}: William Miller?
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, you have an urgent call from a Mr. "Ben Fong-Torres."
{DIALOGUE}: He's holding for you, right now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William takes the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Clerk watches curiously as the kid adopts a new persona.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{META_DATA}: (deep voice)
{DIALOGUE}: Hello.
{META_DATA}: INTERCUT
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JANN'S OFFICE -- SAN FRANCISCO -- AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On a rainy day in San Francisco, Ben Fong-Torres stands in the copy-strewn office of the young editor/publisher JANN WENNER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several other editors are also present in the background, including David Felton with cigarette-holder in mouth, and a prep-school Fact-Checker named ALLISON.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEN
{DIALOGUE}: Congratulations.
{DIALOGUE}: It's gonna be a cover.
{DIALOGUE}: Neal Preston will shoot 'em next week in L.A. we need you back in San Francisco tomorrow.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll finish the story here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William is overwhelmed with many emotions, fear topping the list.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEN (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: You can tell the band.
{DIALOGUE}: Allison, our fact checker, needs you to transmit whatever you have of the story, tonight, now, along with your notes.
{DIALOGUE}: There is a mojo at the Daily News they'll let us use -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: Mojo?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEN
{DIALOGUE}: A mojo.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a very modern machine that transmits pages over the telephone.
{DIALOGUE}: It only takes eighteen Minutes a page...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 126A EXT. NEW YORK STREETS -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of feet on pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William looks at addresses, hustling to the Daily News office.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 126B INT. DAILY NEWS COPY STATION -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William tears pages from his notebook and feeds them into the large and clunky earliest model fax machine -- "The Mojo."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear David Bowie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "The Jean Genie."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A127 EXT. MAX'S KANSAS CITY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William weaves, exhausted, into the Stillwater press party at this legendary New York nightspot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Doorman, who checks i.d.s, sees the kid and expresses great doubt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE
{DIALOGUE}: He's okay, he's with us -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hope shoves him past the Guard, and sends him into a very mature new world.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 127 INT. MAX'S KANSAS CITY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The famous hub of New York rock and roll.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A strong whiff of decadence mixes with youthful naivete.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not a hippie in sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William walks through, looking for familiar faces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Overhead we hear Stillwater.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "If You Say Nothing."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The party is filled with scenesters, long silver-haired glamsters, some British journalists, and many hunched young skinny bodies in leather jackets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell grabs him by the arm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: Ah ha!
{DIALOGUE}: There you are, ya little fucker.
{DIALOGUE}: Come on --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: I have some good news.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: -- I'll piss to that.
{DIALOGUE}: Follow me.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A128 INT. MAX'S BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They enter the small bathroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell bolts the door, faces the urinal and pees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His own music throbs in the next room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: Dennis Hope took me aside, and wants to manage Me solo.
{DIALOGUE}: Says to lose the band by February.
{DIALOGUE}: Should I do it?
{DIALOGUE}: I have no perspective anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William pees in silence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: At what point do I just take the hint?
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody Loves this band.
{DIALOGUE}: People like us, do they love us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: I do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{META_DATA}: (then pissed)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh - get this - somebody told Penny Lane I sold her for beer.
