{DIALOGUE}: It's Jeff who told her, right?
{DIALOGUE}: Not you, right?
{DIALOGUE}: None of these guys can just calm down and be a fuckin adult.
{DIALOGUE}: Now she's here, freaking out.
{DIALOGUE}: Leslie can smell it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{META_DATA}: (exiting)
{DIALOGUE}: Wait.
{DIALOGUE}: I've got something to tell -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But he finds himself trailing Russell to the back room bar.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 128 INT. GIRL'S BATHROOM - NIGHT - SAME TIME
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leslie in the bathroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Penny enters and watches her discreetly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stand together, side-by-side at the mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leslie looks once, turns and then turns back at Penny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She knows.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 129 INT. BACKROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William sits with the band.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Over Jeff's head, Penny hangs nearby, at the outskirts, drinking and dancing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They share a look, feigning casualty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: You guys -- you guys --
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You're gonna be on the cover of Rolling Stone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stunned and overwhelmed, the band waits a beat, lets it sink in... and goes wild.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell, stunned too, looks at the kid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's big news.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jeff stands immediately, eyes moist, glass raised.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{META_DATA}: (tears welling, instantly)
{DIALOGUE}: The cover of Rolling Stone.
{DIALOGUE}: And we made it together.
