{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Penny wears her green coat, large sunglasses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sorts through her many partial tickets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are both so tired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She shakes off her coat -- she's suddenly very hot -- and he grabs it and loops it through her bags.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's irritable, and ready to go home.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 143 INT. AIRPORT GATE - MORNING
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PENNY
{META_DATA}: (baring her soul)
{DIALOGUE}: When I was 14, my Mom and her boyfriend took me to a Rolling Stones concert - and I freaked out and I rushed up to the front of the stage and then a thousand people had the same idea at the same time and I was getting crushed.
{DIALOGUE}: And I couldn't breathe and that thought flashed through me - almost like a car accident - I thought I might die.
{DIALOGUE}: And it was in the middle of "Midnight Rambler" and Keith Richards saw me.
{DIALOGUE}: And he came over, and came to the front of the stage, and he pulled me out.
{DIALOGUE}: And they took me backstage and they gave me coke with ice and a - and a lemon.
{DIALOGUE}: And I never went home.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: What about your Mom?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PENNY
{DIALOGUE}: She always said - "Marry Up."
