{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is no one to share the joke with.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then a few blurry memories come back to her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She gestures to him... understanding him more fully... as he disappears.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 145 INT. AIRPORT TERMINAL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William walks alongside her plane, moving from terminal window to terminal window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catching her glance again, he's picking up steam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What's she saying?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 146 INT. PLANE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She keeps watching as he runs alongside, still keeping up with her plane.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She now fully remembers, and places her outstretched fingers on the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She mouths the words: I'll see you back home!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON WINDOW
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He us running through her fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON WILLIAM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Who can run no further.
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 147 INT. BAND PLANE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell and William are in mid-interview.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kid's microphone is out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a little bit of a rough flight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William wears the same clothes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
