{DIALOGUE}: Just Rapping.
{DIALOGUE}: Bob Dylan!
{DIALOGUE}: I kept looking for you.
{DIALOGUE}: I was going to introduce you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kid feels pain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: What happened to you last night?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILLIAM
{DIALOGUE}: It's a log story.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sharp jolt of turbulence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Russell begins pounding on the card table in rhythm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{META_DATA}: (singing Buddy Holly)
{DIALOGUE}: "Peggy Sure... Peggy Sue... "
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DICK
{DIALOGUE}: Please.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: "Pretty pretty pretty pretty Peggy Sue... "
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment of laughter, and then bam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jeff's drink rises and suspends briefly in mid-air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The plane takes another mighty knock.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: We shouldn't be here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{DIALOGUE}: Doris, we miss you!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fear is creeping in around the edges.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William, already an uneasy flier, looks down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PILOT'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: This is Craig, your pilot.
{DIALOGUE}: It appears we've caught the edge of that electrical storm we were trying to outrun.
{DIALOGUE}: Buckle up tight now.
{DIALOGUE}: We're gonna do our best to getcha out of this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rocking of the plane worsens, as all buckle up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: "Electrical storm?"
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL
{META_DATA}: (strapping in for a roller coaster)
{DIALOGUE}: Rock and roll.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sky darkens abruptly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: William looks up, increasingly nervous, stares straight ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The plane suddenly drops and stabilizes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everyone is silent but Russell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUSSELL (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Wooooooo Baby!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later, an ashen-faced CO-PILOT emerges, balancing himself with hands on the ceiling of the shuddering plane.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CO-PILOT
{DIALOGUE}: We're gonna try to land in Tupelo.
{DIALOGUE}: We're going to have to cut the inside lighting for the next several minutes.
{DIALOGUE}: We found a field to land in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kid notices Silent Ed is rubbing a small crucifix.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENNIS HOPE
{DIALOGUE}: A field?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEFF
{DIALOGUE}: I can't breathe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Push in on Russell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear a series of unfamiliar electrical sounds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The plane screwballs through the sky.
